==========================================================================
STEP 0 — Pre-flight check (added 2026-05-13)
==========================================================================

Before dropping any trigger, verify the runtime is healthy. If anything is missing, attempt one auto-restart; if that fails, DM Joshua and stop. Do NOT drop a trigger if the watcher isn't actually running — the trigger will sit unprocessed and you'll waste 45 minutes polling.

**Check 1 — Parallels VM running:**
```bash
/usr/local/bin/prlctl list --all | grep -E 'running.*Windows 11'
```
Expected: `running  -  Windows 11`. If absent, the VM isn't started. DM Joshua and stop — starting a VM remotely is not reliable enough to do unattended.

**Check 2 — bravo_watcher.ahk process alive:**
```bash
/usr/local/bin/prlctl exec '{7dc84f03-4e68-4f43-9596-bf8a7dfb8e0a}' --current-user wmic process where 'name="AutoHotkey64.exe"' get ProcessId,CommandLine
```
Expected: one of the AHK processes has `bravo_watcher.ahk` in its command line. If not, auto-restart with:
```bash
/usr/local/bin/prlctl exec '{7dc84f03-4e68-4f43-9596-bf8a7dfb8e0a}' --current-user cmd /c start "" /B "C:/Program Files/AutoHotkey/v2/AutoHotkey64.exe" "Y:/Documents/Claude/Projects/Bravo Data Extraction/bravo_watcher.ahk"
```
Wait 5s, re-check. If still missing, DM Joshua and stop.

**Check 3 — BravoAutoLogin.ahk process alive:**
Same `wmic` check; look for `BravoAutoLogin.ahk` in command line. If missing, auto-restart with:
```bash
/usr/local/bin/prlctl exec '{7dc84f03-4e68-4f43-9596-bf8a7dfb8e0a}' --current-user cmd /c start "" /B "C:/Program Files/AutoHotkey/v2/AutoHotkey64.exe" "C:/Users/joshuadavis/AppData/Roaming/Microsoft/Windows/Start Menu/Programs/Startup/BravoAutoLogin.ahk"
```
Wait 5s, re-check. If still missing, DM Joshua and continue anyway — the watcher's `RecoverFromAutoLock` handles most login-screen cases without BravoAutoLogin, just less robustly.

**Check 4 — watcher.last_started.txt timestamp is recent:**
```bash
cat '/Users/joshuadavis/Documents/Claude/Projects/Bravo Data Extraction/logs/watcher.last_started.txt'
```
If the timestamp is more than 7 days old, the watcher may have stale code from before recent patches. Restart it anyway (kill+relaunch) to pick up any updates. This is cheap insurance.

**Check 5 — Trigger queue is empty:**
```bash
ls '/Users/joshuadavis/Documents/Claude/Projects/Bravo Data Extraction/triggers/' | grep -v '^processed$'
```
Expected: empty. If a trigger is sitting unprocessed, the previous run hung or is in flight. Do not drop another one — DM Joshua, dump the offending trigger filename, and stop.

Only if all five checks pass, proceed to Step 1.

