STEP 1B — Drop FIVE sequential end-of-month triggers (one per store)
==========================================================================

After the main trigger above is dropped, also drop five SEPARATE single-store
triggers for `end-of-month` — one per store, spaced 90 seconds apart. This
is the per-store source for the `monday-store-rankings` 8-metric leaderboard.

Rationale: chaining all 5 stores in one trigger reliably hangs Bravo's End
of Month preview (the report's matrix layout + 5 pages of pagination puts
the WPF preview into a "Not Responding" state mid-export when run back-to-
back). Single-store invocations are reliable; 90s of breathing room
between them lets Bravo's preview teardown finish before the next store.

For each store in ["CUL", "HAR", "LEX", "ROA", "WAY"]:

```json
{
  "id": "monday-eom-<STORE>-YYYY-MM-DD",
  "requested_at": "2026-05-12T05:32:00-04:00",
  "reports": [
    {"name": "end-of-month", "stores": ["<STORE>"], "date": "<FIRST_OF_MONTH>..<YESTERDAY>"}
  ]
}
```

Drop sequence (orchestrator pseudocode):

```
for STORE in CUL, HAR, LEX, ROA, WAY:
    write triggers/monday-eom-<STORE>-YYYY-MM-DD.json
    poll results/monday-eom-<STORE>-YYYY-MM-DD.result.json (timeout 5 min)
    sleep 90 seconds
```

Each store's run produces `output/<END_DATE>_<STORE>_end-of-month.csv` (~11 KB).
The `monday-store-rankings` chained SKILL reads all 5 to build the rankings.

After the result JSON arrives, **copy each chekkit-inactives CSV into the shared stash** so the Tuesday chekkit-weekly-review-requests task can find it without re-pulling:

